reviews.review_text: Better than remembered I remember being at this show and not being terribly impressed. Perhaps I was distracted, cause the playing is good. West L.A. is lively and the second set is worth a listen. Playing has a nice jam with everyone jelling well. Listen closely, around 10:04 Bobby starts to play a James Bond theme. Crazy fingers has a nice delicate quality to it. For me it was a nice surprise.
